During a visit to Augusta Victoria Hospital in Jerusalem, President Joe Biden expressed his appreciation for nurses and the important role they play in healthcare. He shared personal experiences of his own health struggles and the impact nurses had on him and his family. Biden announced that the United States will commit an additional $100 million to support Palestinian hospitals, including Augusta Victoria Hospital, as part of the country's commitment to the health and dignity of the Palestinian people. He also called for other countries to contribute to this cause. Biden emphasized the importance of access to healthcare and pledged to work with Palestinian leadership, the Israeli government, and international partners to ensure the sustainability and quality of healthcare services in East Jerusalem. The President concluded his remarks by thanking the hospital staff for their dedication and care for patients.